  "prompt": "My girlfriend talks to her ex crush frequently. how do I deal with it or talk to her?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions for handling this situation:\n\n1. Communicate openly and honestly\n- Express your feelings calmly and without accusation\n- Use \"I\" statements like \"I feel uncomfortable when...\"\n- Listen to her perspective\n\n2. Understand the nature of their communication\n- Ask about the frequency and type of interactions\n- Determine if there are any inappropriate boundaries\n- Try to understand their relationship objectively\n\n3. Set clear boundaries together\n- Discuss what makes you uncomfortable\n- Establish mutual relationship guidelines\n- Be reasonable and fair\n\n4. Build trust\n- Avoid being overly jealous or controlling\n- Show confidence in your relationship\n- Focus on strengthening your connection\n\n5. Watch for red flags\n- Is the communication secretive?\n- Are there emotional or flirtatious undertones?\n- Does she respect your feelings?\n\n6. Consider your comfort level\n- Reflect on whether this is a dealbreaker for you\n- Be honest about your emotional needs\n- Decide if you can accept the situation\n\n7. Seek compromise\n- Find a solution that makes you both comfortable\n- Consider reducing communication frequency\n- Potentially include transparency about interactions\n\nRemember to approach the conversation with respect, empathy, and a desire to understand each other.",
